      body: "## Elba: Mediterranean Diving at Its Best\n\n**Elba Island** lies off the coast of Tuscany and is one of Italy's finest diving destinations. Clear waters, varied sites—from wrecks to protected reserves—and rich **marine life** make it a must for divers.\n\n## Top Dive Sites\n\n**Pomonte wreck** is a highlight: a cargo ship resting in shallow water, ideal for all levels. **Scoglietto marine reserve** offers protected reefs and **Posidonia** meadows. **Capo d'Enfola** combines caves and walls with groupers and morays. Other spots include **Fetovaia**, **Cavoli**, and **Marina di Campo**, each with distinct character.\n\n## Marine Life and Visibility\n\nYou can expect **dentex**, **sea bream**, **octopus**, and **moray eels**. In season, **barracuda** and **tuna** appear. **Posidonia oceanica** meadows host juveniles and invertebrates. Visibility often reaches 20–30 m in summer.\n\n## Best Season and Accessibility\n\nThe **best season** runs from May to October; July–September is warmest. Elba is reached by ferry from **Piombino** (about 1 hour). Once on the island, dive centres in **Marina di Campo**, **Fetovaia**, and **Pomonte** organise daily boats. Suitable for beginners and advanced divers.",
